Fetch and merge with current branch

$ git clone https://YOURGITHUBUSERNAME@github.com/YOURGITHUBUSERNAME/helloworld
$ cd helloworld
$ git remote add upstream https://github.com/ddexter-learning/helloworld
$ git fetch upstream
$ git merge upstream/master
$ git push
License

Download all project files. Open the LICENSE file in a text editor. Replace all occurrences of [Full name] with your name. Save the file and replace the original LICENSE file with this one. Commit this change to your hello-world repository and push to GitHub.

$ git add LICENSE
$ git commit -m "Used my real name"
$ git push
Create a file in your hello-world repo called CONTRIBUTORS. Add your name to this file and commit it.

$ git add CONTRIBUTORS
$ git commit -m "Add myself to CONTRIBUTORS"
$ git push
$ git checkout -b bug-fix
Switched to a new branch 'bug-fix'
$ git branch
* bug-fix
  master
$ git checkout master
Switched to branch 'master'

Your branch is up to date with 'origin/master'.
$ git merge bug-fix
Updating f42c576..9e8f217
Fast-forward

Create a branch

On GitHub.com, navigate to the main page of the repository.
Under your repository name, click  to open the drop-down menu.
Click New pull request.
Click the checkboxes next to the branches you wish to merge, then click Merge pull request.
Click Confirm merge, then Delete branch.
A branch is like a save point for your code. Imagine you change 1,000 lines all related to adding a login feature, then 2 days later realized it was a bad idea and you want to throw away all those changes, but you dont want to do so for the rest of your code? This is what branches are for.

Create a new branch

$ git checkout -b add-login
Switched to a new branch 'add-login'
You are on a branch yet to be pushed to, and can be considered private


$ git branch
* add-login
  master
You can push a branch to GitHub just like your master branch:

$ git push origin add-login
There you have it!
How are you feeling?

In the past 2 weeks, you have learned how to:

Fork and clone GitHub repositories
Create new branches
Open and merge pull requests

If you have any questions or get stuck, miss a step, or just want to show off what you made, post it on Piazza!
